post_text:
Dragon Families,
Labor Day weekend is not a time to let down our guard. When celebrating the holiday and visiting with family and friends, please continue to be vigilant- wash your hands, wear a face covering and social distance, whenever possible. We appreciate your cooperation so we can remain in school.

We will continue to analyze our local, county and state data and work with our partners at the Health Department and City of Purcell to make a determination about rotating the A/B schedule. We will keep you posted in the coming days. Students will return to school as normal on September 8, 2020-September 11, 2020. Have a safe weekend! #MaskUpOK

post_text: High School Football Fans: Join us tomorrow night for a 3-way scrimmage with Anadarko and Little Axe at Conger Field. Our 9th grade will begin at 6:00 followed by the Varsity team at 7:00. We ask that all spectators wear a face covering upon entering our stadium, while walking to your seat, concession, restrooms, and upon exiting the stadium. Also, we ask that you to maintain physical distancing when seated by allowing for at least 2 seats between non-family groups. These measures are very important in our efforts to keep our schools open and our activities running. We appreciate your cooperation. Go Dragons!

May 4 at 1:30 PM ¬∑

Parents / Grandparents / Guardians of the Senior Class of 2020,

I am extending the date of Senior Send-Offs (formerly Senior Ads) until the end of May to give you more time to decide if you would like to purchase one for your graduating Senior. We still have a few spots available.

If you have any questions, please email me at hilgerd@purcellps.org

post_text:
Purcell High School has set a tentative date for the 2020 Prom on July 16th from 8-11pm at the Grand Canadian Theater. This is subject to change depending on CDC regulations. Our first and utmost concern is for the safety of our students and staff. We will inform you at least a month prior to any cancellation. Only the students that were previously signed up to go to the PHS Prom may attend and will not be charged again. Appropriate dress code needs to be followed but may be formal or semi-formal. Any questions please contact Zoe Swift or Krysta Matthews. swiftz@purcellps.org
matthewsk@purcellps.org

post_text:
As we all continue to follow recommendations from the CDC, Purcell High School Prom has been canceled. As much as we regret this, our students, and their safety, will always be our number one priority.
We will be issuing full refunds on all purchased prom tickets. Information on how to get your money back will be following this announcement within the next few days.
We know this will be a huge disappointment to many of our students and their families but we hope everyone understands this decision was made only with the students and community in mind. We appreciate your understanding and hope you all continue to stay safe and healthy. Please direct any questions to Zoe Swift at swiftz@purcellps.org or Krysta Matthews at matthewsk@purcellps.org.
--
